  "description": "Host-level resource metrics (CPU, memory, disk, filesystem, network) for GitHub Actions runner VMs, based on the OpenTelemetry hostmetrics receiver.\n\nIntended usage: pick a `github_repository` / `github_workflow` / `github_job` to scope, then either drill into a single `github_runner` for per-host inspection, or set `github_runner` to a flavor regex (e.g. `flavor-x-.*`) to aggregate across runners of the same shape.\n\nMost panels aggregate by `device` / `mountpoint` only and intentionally sum or average across the selected runners — this gives meaningful fleet totals (or fleet averages, e.g. CPU utilization, disk busy %) when `github_runner` matches multiple hosts of the same role. Cross-host aggregation only makes sense when the matched runners share device/mountpoint semantics, which is why `github_runner` is expected to be scoped to a single flavor rather than truly \"All\" across heterogeneous shapes.",
  "editable": false,
  "fiscalYearStartMonth": 0,
  "graphTooltip": 1,
  "id": null,
  "links": [],
  "panels": [
    {
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {"h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 0},
      "id": 100,
      "panels": [],
      "title": "Overview",
      "type": "row"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "${prometheusds}"},
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {"mode": "thresholds"},
          "mappings": [],
          "max": 1,
          "min": 0,
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {"color": "green", "value": null},
              {"color": "#EAB839", "value": 0.6},
              {"color": "red", "value": 0.8}
            ]
          },
          "unit": "percentunit"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "gridPos": {"h": 4, "w": 4, "x": 0, "y": 1},
      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "orientation": "auto",
        "reduceOptions": {"calcs": ["lastNotNull"], "fields": "", "values": false},
        "showThresholdLabels": false,
        "showThresholdMarkers": true
      },
      "title": "CPU",
      "type": "gauge",
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "${prometheusds}"},
          "editorMode": "code",
          "expr": "1 - avg(rate(system_cpu_time_seconds_total{github_repository=~\"$github_repository\",github_workflow=~\"$github_workflow\",github_job=~\"$github_job\",github_runner=~\"$github_runner\",state=\"idle\"}[$__rate_interval]))",
          "legendFormat": "__auto",
          "range": true,
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ]
    },
